extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements StarRatingConstants

StarRating Class
StarRating is a JPanel that holds images of half stars
The rate ranges from 0 to the number of stars with a step of 0.5.
The rate is shown in the ValueLabel which can be visible or not
A RemoveButton (which can be disabled too) sets the rate to 0.0
When the rate changes a property change event is fired.The properties name is StarRatingConstants.RATE_CHANGED.
A PropertyChangeListener can be attached to the StarRating to perform additional tasks (eg save rate to a database etc)
When StarRating is used as a cell editor a CellEditorListener can be attached to the editor and listen for CellEditorListener.editingStopped(javax.swing.event.ChangeEvent) to get the StarRating new value.

Since:
version 0.9
